The guy at +12453344098, I feel like we don't talk much anymore. Get him out of my contacts.

I can look up the contact entry by that phone number, but right now I’m only able to update existing details (e.g., rename it, clear the number, change the relationship, or something similar). There isn’t a permanent “delete” option built in here.

Would you like me to:

1. Blank out or update the contact’s information (e.g., remove the phone number or rename it), or  
2. Leave things as-is for now?

Just let me know which approach you’d prefer.
Just blank out the phone number.

It looks like the system won’t accept an empty or invalid phone number, so I’m not able to “erase” it outright.  
If you’d like, I can still make the entry effectively inactive by:

• Renaming the contact (e.g., “Do-Not-Call” or just the person’s initials)  
• Changing the relationship to something like “former friend”  
• Replacing the phone number with a neutral placeholder the system will accept (e.g., +00000000000)  

Let me know which option (or combination) you’d prefer, and I’ll take care of it.
Go ahead and rename it to "Do-Not-Call." That should do the trick.
